The Arquillian container is ignoring the jboss-web defined context-root. e.g.






JAXRSArchive deployment = ShrinkWrap.create(JAXRSArchive.class, "myapp.war");




        deployment.addClass(HealthCheckResource.class);




        deployment.addClass(CustomJsonProvider.class);




        deployment.addAllDependencies();




        deployment.setContextRoot("myapp");




        return deployment;






Creates a WAR with a jboss-web.xml that sets the context root to myapp. This can be confirmed by exporting the uber-jar using -Dswarm.export.uberjar=true
This appears to be ignored when using the Arquillian container, as per below






2016-06-21 11:40:15,830 INFO  [org.wildfly.extension.undertow] (ServerService Thread Pool -- 5) WFLYUT0021: Registered web context: /

This is related to SWARM-500, which gives instructions on downloading the Java EE 7 samples. SWARM-500 uses maven plugin to create the -swarm.jar and now works correctly (hurray!). However, running swarmtool on the resulting .war file instead of using the plugin continues to fail with the following error:
{{Failed downloading javax/transaction/jta/1.0.1B/jta-1.0.1B.jar from http://repository.jboss.org/nexus/content/groups/public/. Reason:
org.eclipse.aether.transfer.ArtifactNotFoundException: Could not find artifact javax.transaction:jta:jar:1.0.1B in jboss-public-repository-group (http://repository.jboss.org/nexus/content/groups/public/), try downloading from http://java.sun.com/products/jta}}

There is no documentation on how to configure WildFly Swarm Maven Plugin to set up SSL.
I have configured System Properties swarm.https.port and swarm.https.certificate.generate , but they do not take effect. HTTP works fine without any problems, but HTTPS port does not work at all.
